Res is the nominative singular for "thing" or "object." Rebus is its ablative plural: "by means of things" (shall ye solve this puzzle or is this game or other writing constructed).

In English, the plural of rebus, should one need it, would be rebuses, with the Latin word having jumped into English as a singular noun; however, "rebus puzzles," "rebus crosswords," or the like would be more elegant as well as less painful to those who know the etymology.

